By: Michael Sendivogius
---
In metals, then, as in all other things, there is only one first substance, but
the universal substance is modified in a vast variety of ways, according to the
course of its subsequent development. Thus one thing is the mother of all
things. This great fact ought always to be borne in mind in studying the works
of the Sages; for nothing but mistakes and disappointment can result from a
slavishly literal interpretation of their books.
